      <memberdef kind="define" id="group__mspi__devicetree_1ga501b2e19e358083f2b47838cde58a676" prot="public" static="no">
        <name>MSPI_CE_CONTROL_INIT</name>
        <param><defname>node_id</defname></param>
        <param><defname>delay_</defname></param>
        <initializer>	{                                                                                         \
		.gpio = <ref refid="group__mspi__devicetree_1ga0a91ef9392be4493ede6cea607ee8728" kindref="member">MSPI_DEV_CE_GPIOS_DT_SPEC_GET</ref>(node_id), .delay = (delay_),                \
	}</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize and get a pointer to a <computeroutput><ref refid="structmspi__ce__control" kindref="compound">mspi_ce_control</ref></computeroutput> from a devicetree node identifier. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This helper is useful for initializing a device on a MSPI bus. It initializes a struct <ref refid="structmspi__ce__control" kindref="compound">mspi_ce_control</ref> and returns a pointer to it. Here, <computeroutput>node_id</computeroutput> is a node identifier for a MSPI device, not a MSPI controller.</para>
<para>Example devicetree fragment:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".devicetree"><codeline><highlight class="normal">mspi@abcd0001<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>ce-gpios<sp/>=<sp/>&lt;&amp;gpio0<sp/>1<sp/>GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW&gt;;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>mspidev:<sp/>mspi-device@0<sp/>{<sp/>...<sp/>};</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">};</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Example usage:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".c"><codeline><highlight class="keyword">struct<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structmspi__ce__control" kindref="compound">mspi_ce_control</ref><sp/>ctrl<sp/>=</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><ref refid="group__mspi__devicetree_1ga501b2e19e358083f2b47838cde58a676" kindref="member">MSPI_CE_CONTROL_INIT</ref>(<ref refid="group__devicetree-generic-id_1gab7d23294a6bf7fd44a98b48ec47d8a79" kindref="member">DT_NODELABEL</ref>(mspidev),<sp/>2);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>This example is equivalent to:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".c"><codeline><highlight class="keyword">struct<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structmspi__ce__control" kindref="compound">mspi_ce_control</ref><sp/>ctrl<sp/>=<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.<ref refid="structmspi__ce__control_1a1f1b6f5583abc08c8c7fae95e1a29a7a" kindref="member">gpio</ref><sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="group__mspi__devicetree_1ga0a91ef9392be4493ede6cea607ee8728" kindref="member">MSPI_DEV_CE_GPIOS_DT_SPEC_GET</ref>(<ref refid="group__devicetree-generic-id_1gab7d23294a6bf7fd44a98b48ec47d8a79" kindref="member">DT_NODELABEL</ref>(mspidev)),</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.delay<sp/>=<sp/>2,</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">};</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>node_id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Devicetree node identifier for a device on a MSPI bus </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>delay_</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The <computeroutput>delay</computeroutput> field to set in the <computeroutput><ref refid="structmspi__ce__control" kindref="compound">mspi_ce_control</ref></computeroutput> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>a pointer to the <computeroutput><ref refid="structmspi__ce__control" kindref="compound">mspi_ce_control</ref></computeroutput> structure </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
